SIMPLE: secondhand
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Secondhand
<hw>Sec"ond*hand`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Not
original or primary; received from another; <as>as, <ex>secondhand</ex>
information</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

<p><q>They have but a <qex>secondhand</qex> or implicit knowledge.</q>
<rj><qau>Locke.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Not new; already or previously possessed or used by
another; <as>as, a <ex>secondhand</ex> book, garment</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>At second hand</b></col>. <cd>See <er>Hand</er>,
<pos>n.</pos>, 10.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Secondly</ent>⟦br⟧
